lead_paragraph: SUICIDE.--A young man named Greenaway, committed suicide, on Monday, the 15th instant, at Youngstown, in Niagara County. He discharged a gun, loaded with buck shot, into his neck. The cause is not known. THE FIRES IN MAINE.--A letter from our Machias correspondent, dated 24th inst., says: "We had a fine rain last night, which so far extinguished the raging fires that they will probably do no further damage this season."--Boston Adv.
